<title>USA: Phoenix to take charge of $0.03/shr.</title>
<headline>Phoenix to take charge of $0.03/shr.</headline>
<dateline>SAN JOSE, Calif. 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Phoenix Technologies Ltd said on Thursday it will take a non-cash charge of about $800,000 or $0.03 per share for research and development expenditures and acquisition costs for the purchase of Nihon Joho Kenkyujo K.K., a Tokyo-based software company.</p>
<p>The $1.4 million acquisition, recorded as a purchase transaction, was effective on Dec. 27, 1996, and will not have a material impact on the operating results for the company's quarter ended Dec. 31, 1996.</p>
<p>Phoenix Technologies said it supplies standards-based compatibility software to the personal computer industry.</p>
